text:
StellarAlgo is a customer cloud platform
for the live audience,

sports and entertainment business,
including enthusiast brands and sponsors.

We consolidate and process our customers
first party and secondary data,

and we enrich it through machine
learning models.
StellarAlgo was founded in 2016.

Since then we've experienced
exponential growth.

AWS provides the foundation
for the StellarAlgo data products

that allow our customers
to feel confident in their availability,

the performance,
and the security of their data.

The benefit that our customers receive
from the StellarAlgo

products is an ability to engage
with their fan base better.

StellarAlgo provides the
ability for them to focus

and do what they're passionate about
and what will generate the most value
for them.
Similarly, AWS allows StellarAlgo's

product engineering team
to focus on what it's passionate about.

It's built into our culture
of intellectual curiosity.

Our engineers really enjoy the challenges
of leveraging what AWS

engineers have developed to achieve either
increased margin

or lower the cost of the products that we
provide to our customers, through this innovation.
StellarAlgo is enriching our customers
fan data in excess of 150 million fans.
And we have to analyze more than
50 billion fan interactions.
It's critical that we develop and innovate patterns
It's critical that we develop and innovate patterns

that allow us to achieve a SaaS scale
business without also exponentially
adding skilled engineering resources. And so with AWS,
what we're seeing is that being able to do more with less,
and that's a critical part of strategy in our growth.
